Join us here for a PREVIEW of our daily one-hour RUMBLE show. 
To continue watching the show in full, join me exclusively over on RUMBLE: https://bit.ly/SF544-live

Trump’s AI-generated vision of a redeveloped Gaza raises questions about U.S. influence in the region, while Ukraine officially agrees to a resource deal with the U.S., fueling debates over economic control and war funding. At the same time, fears of a new pandemic grow as reports emerge of a coronavirus strain originating from Wuhan, reigniting scrutiny over gain-of-function research and government responses. Meanwhile, immigration policy takes center stage as Trump announces a controversial $5 million “gold card” for wealthy migrants, and the Tucker-Crenshaw feud escalates after a hot mic moment expose
title: AI Visions, War Deals, and the Next Big Lockdown? – SF544
